00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 To justify Augustine, Rose argues that his theology

392
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:13,000
 was too conditioned by personal experience.

393
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:19,000
 And St. Augustine would have responded by the experience of grace,

394
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:21,000
 not personal experience.

395
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:25,000
 At the same time, Rose argues that Augustine was too Western

396
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:28,000
 and therefore wanted to subordinate the doctrine of God

397
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:32,000
 to the laws of human logic.

